I am a seasoned professional seeking a senior IT leadership position in project and program
management, with a particular interest in artificial intelligence (AI) and deep learning. Throughout my
tenure, I have actively pursued projects and research involving the application of AI to the
development of decision support systems and prediction analysis models.
With a solid background in the Information Technology industry, I have spent years conquering the
complexities of AI and deep learning techniques. I have effectively implemented projects and
conducted research that leverage the power of artificial intelligence to improve decision-making
processes and enable accurate prediction analysis.
My AI expertise includes the development of AI-driven decision support systems and the application of
deep learning techniques for predictive modeling, among other areas. I have a history of delivering
effective solutions that leverage AI algorithms to extract insights, optimize processes, and drive data-
driven decisions.
In my pursuit of a senior IT leadership position, I am anxious to contribute my in-depth knowledge of
artificial intelligence and deep learning to organizations seeking to harness the potential of these
cutting-edge technologies. I am passionate about using AI to drive innovation, improve operational
efficiency, and unleash new growth and success opportunities.
Professional Experience
 Ministry of Interior – Abu Dhabi Police (October 2010 – Present)
During my tenure at the Ministry of Interior and Abu Dhabi Police, I was involved in numerous
initiatives and programs that brought about a significant transformation in strategic and operational
police and leadership operations. This transformation has enabled Abu Dhabi Police GHQ to attain
advanced international standards, thereby garnering Abu Dhabi City the prestigious title of "Safest City
in the World" for six consecutive years.
We have effectively enhanced the customer experience through the implementation of innovative
systems and programs, resulting in a customer satisfaction rate of over 97% over the past five years.
The integration of artificial intelligence systems, decision support systems, future foresight systems,
and Internet of Things (IoT) technologies in both the operational and leadership aspects of police work
has had a significant impact on employee performance.
In my role, I have contributed actively to these initiatives and systems, beginning with strategic
planning and engaging with leaders to determine the desired impact and required changes. I align
projects closely with strategic objectives, identify internal and external stakeholders, and pursue
potential partnerships to ensure the successful implementation of projects. This includes
benchmarking, researching market-available platforms, identifying suitable suppliers and companies,
and executing the project. Continuously, I assess the impact of the project, identify areas for
enhancement, and devise plans for future project enhancement.
During my more than 12-year tenure with Abu Dhabi Police and the Ministry of the Interior, I have held
a variety of positions, including computer engineer, programmer, trainer, project manager, and IT
consultant.
